sleep is a phenomenon that affects all animals, even insects. And it's a state where you're actually different from the wake state because you don't react to stimuli in the same sense as when you're awake. And there are many ways to classify sleep. And one is the way how you react to stimuli, and the other one is actually to measure what is happening in the brain with the EEG, for example
